                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="initial">Red and blue opening initials.</decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions><p>Leaves of paper, two and seven, respectively, are inserted at the
                        front and the back of the original manuscript.</p>
                     <p>In the bottom margin of fol. 130, a hand from the seventeenth century added:
                           <q>Henricus Christianus <lb/>Blichfeldius Arhuſien<lb/>ſis</q>.</p>
                     <p>On the recto of the last of the seven paper leaves, a pen trial containing
                        the name <q>Meckell</q> is found. On the verso of the second front paper
                        leaf some stanzas in French from the seventeenth century were added.</p>
                     <p>To fol. 1r various initials, the years 1571 and 1609 together with a text in
                        Greek and Latin have been added. A coat of arms (three roses) hanging on a
                        branch and, below this, some sequence of numbers, are found on fol.
                     1v.</p></additions>
